      </div>
      <div class="overlay-header-body">
        On 6 November 2024, we presented a sound composition created in Hamburg-Schnelsen as part of a literature festival in a church. By integrating field recordings and tape loops recorded on site, we designed an immersive listening experience specifically created for the spatial and acoustic atmosphere of the performance venue. In this context, we combine the warm, unamplified sounds of the church organ with audio tracks played back in a wide stereo field. The aim was to explore new acoustic spatial concepts through the interplay of different sound sources and to immerse the listener in a multi-layered soundscape. <span class="intro-arrow" id="dot-organ"><b>→</b></span>
        <br>
